{"name":"Ranged Combat-Botch","img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","description":"Optionally, instead of always suffering 1D6+2 DP for a botch, you can roll on this table.","results":[{"_id":"cWg4hhULa2t8clAr","type":0,"text":"The weapon is irreparably destroyed. If the weapon is unbreakable, it falls to the ground.","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":2,"rangeH":2},{"_id":"tIKaoYDSkqMBjvpm","type":0,"text":"You cannot use the weapon until it is repaired. If the weapon is unbreakable, it falls to the ground.","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":3,"rangeH":3},{"_id":"txSHKVkr1xbLR7XU","type":0,"text":"The weapon is damaged. All checks against ranged combat suffer a penalty of 4 until the weapon is repaired. If the weapon is unbreakable, it falls to the ground.","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":4,"rangeH":4},{"_id":"9OMCCXCFiEgq0alB","type":0,"text":"The weapon falls to the ground.","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":5,"rangeH":5},{"_id":"A0TRFdWwU2MYytem","type":0,"text":"Hits a friend or an innocent bystander, determined randomly. If no such target is near, you hurt Yourself. The weapon inflicts normal damage, including the usual damage bonus.","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":6,"rangeH":6},{"_id":"yrboAegh9Ju1dGC7","type":0,"text":"The shot misses in a spectacular way and hits an object (shoots down a shop sign, breaks a window, or some such thing).","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":7,"rangeH":7},{"_id":"bPjOYHCVL3eKHvCt","type":0,"text":"The hero experiences a sudden back spasm and suffers a level of the condition Pain for the next 3 combat rounds.","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":8,"rangeH":8},{"_id":"Fo25J2SPOodMWl5C","type":0,"text":"Take two complete combat rounds to make your weapon usable again.","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":9,"rangeH":9},{"_id":"mFhcXmAA9Pcq4XAg","type":0,"text":"You are concentrating too hard on aiming or are otherwise occupied with the weapon and cannot make defenses until your next action.","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":10,"rangeH":10},{"_id":"J8wdZ3JSDCEoKsCW","type":0,"text":"You injure yourself and suffer damage. Take the weapon’s normal damage, including the damage bonus.","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":11,"rangeH":11},{"_id":"0TejvR31LVkvzmzp","type":0,"text":"You injure yourself badly and suffer damage. Roll the weapon’s normal damage, including the damage bonus, and double the result.","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":12,"rangeH":12}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DuPORyMy1IVtkIcO":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.s3YHPkVNXwfPzxy7"}},"_id":"TMktUN3q4cHC2lrn"}
{"name":"Spell-Botch","img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","description":"Magical botches are usually unpleasant and can be extremely dangerous.","results":[{"_id":"cWg4hhULa2t8clAr","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster’s mind switches bodies with the nearest creature larger than a rat for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":2,"rangeH":2},{"_id":"tIKaoYDSkqMBjvpm","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster is Condition Annoyed by Minor Spirits for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":3,"rangeH":3},{"_id":"txSHKVkr1xbLR7XU","type":0,"text":"The spell affects a different, random target instead, as determined by the GM.","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":4,"rangeH":4},{"_id":"9OMCCXCFiEgq0alB","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster turns into a small animal of the GM’s choosing for 1D6 hours.","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":5,"rangeH":5},{"_id":"A0TRFdWwU2MYytem","type":0,"text":"All remaining AE leaves the spellcaster’s body and manifests as a rain of colorful sparks, illusionary butterflies, and small rainbows. The spellcaster regenerates this AE in the usual way.","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":6,"rangeH":6},{"_id":"yrboAegh9Ju1dGC7","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster loses the ability to use AE for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":7,"rangeH":7},{"_id":"bPjOYHCVL3eKHvCt","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster suffers a throbbing headache and a level of the condition Stupor for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":8,"rangeH":8},{"_id":"Fo25J2SPOodMWl5C","type":0,"text":"All remaining AE leaves the spellcaster’s body and jumps to the next closes above the normal maximum. The spellcaster regenerates this AE in the usual way.","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":9,"rangeH":9},{"_id":"mFhcXmAA9Pcq4XAg","type":0,"text":"The spellcaster receives the condition mute for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":10,"rangeH":10},{"_id":"J8wdZ3JSDCEoKsCW","type":0,"text":"All of the spellcaster’s hair takes on a bright color, but grows back in its original color.","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":11,"rangeH":11},{"_id":"0TejvR31LVkvzmzp","type":0,"text":"An ethereal voice speaks from out of thin air, saying “Never do that again!”","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":12,"rangeH":12}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DuPORyMy1IVtkIcO":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.s3YHPkVNXwfPzxy7"}},"_id":"eSEUM9HZQa1iBgqp"}
{"name":"Ceremonies-/Chants-Botch","img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","description":"Karmal botches are usually unpleasant and can be extremely dangerous.","results":[{"_id":"cWg4hhULa2t8clAr","type":0,"text":"All flammable materials are set ablaze in an area of 2D6 square yards (does not affect creatures or the Blessed One’s clothes).","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":2,"rangeH":2},{"_id":"tIKaoYDSkqMBjvpm","type":0,"text":"The liturgical chant has the opposite effect (Banish Darkness creates darkness, a Blessing of Healing causes injury instead, and so on).","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":3,"rangeH":3},{"_id":"txSHKVkr1xbLR7XU","type":0,"text":"The liturgical chant targets someone or something else randomly, as determined by the GM.","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":4,"rangeH":4},{"_id":"9OMCCXCFiEgq0alB","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One suffers strange visions and nightmares for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":5,"rangeH":5},{"_id":"A0TRFdWwU2MYytem","type":0,"text":"A gaze into another Sphere is so intimidating that the Blessed One suffers 3 levels of the condition Fear for the day.","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":6,"rangeH":6},{"_id":"yrboAegh9Ju1dGC7","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One loses the ability to use KP for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":7,"rangeH":7},{"_id":"bPjOYHCVL3eKHvCt","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One receives 4 levels of Rapture.","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":8,"rangeH":8},{"_id":"Fo25J2SPOodMWl5C","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One suffers 3 levels of Confusion for the day and talks nonsense that cannot be remembered later.","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":9,"rangeH":9},{"_id":"mFhcXmAA9Pcq4XAg","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One receives the condition mute for 1D6 day(s).","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":10,"rangeH":10},{"_id":"J8wdZ3JSDCEoKsCW","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One suffers a stigma for the day.","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":11,"rangeH":11},{"_id":"0TejvR31LVkvzmzp","type":0,"text":"The Blessed One’s feet become rooted to the ground, restricting movement and causing the Blessed One to suffer the state bound for 1D6 minutes.","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dsa5/icons/dice/d20mu.svg","rangeL":12,"rangeH":12}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DuPORyMy1IVtkIcO":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.s3YHPkVNXwfPzxy7"}},"_id":"kfChKB9GbkVGfjBZ"}
